  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Chop the <strong>red chilli[es]</strong> roughly (deseed if you can't handle the heat!)</p><p>Peel and roughly chop the <strong>garlic</strong>, <strong>ginger</strong> and <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Bash the <strong>lemongrass</strong> with a <strong>rolling pin </strong>and remove the tough outer layer[s]</p><p>Chop the softer <strong>inner lemongrass core</strong> roughly</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped chilli</strong>, <strong>garlic</strong>, <strong>ginger</strong>, <strong>shallot</strong> and <strong>lemongrass</strong> to a <strong>food processor</strong> with the <strong>ground</strong> <strong>turmeric</strong>, <strong>tamari soy sauce</strong>, <strong>coconut cream </strong>and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>roasted peanuts </strong>(save the rest for garnish!)</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water</strong> and blitz until you're left with a smooth paste – this is your<strong> ayam betutu paste</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1630487693539-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1630487693539-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1630487693539-x700.jpg",
